title: Gossip | Watch: Justin Bieber posts Robbie Keane's video of post match bliss after Ireland beat Germany
text:
Justin Bieber has congratulated, his "brother Keano and the Irish Squad" for beating World Champions Germany 1-0 last night on home soil. GET IN.
Of course, the Irish team celebrated some down time after their spectacular victory by listening to Justin Bieber on the way home on the bus... In the video, Keane can be heard saying "we beat the world champions" - you can almost hear the silent tears of joy streaming down faces in the dark.
Here it is. Robbie Keane and the Irish lads listening to #WhatDoYouMean after the victory pic.twitter.com/SsrWOKconw
— Justin Bieber (@justinbieber) October 9, 2015 Love to my brother Keano and the Irish squad on a big win today. Got this vid of them listening to #WhatDoYouMean after the win. Love it.
— Justin Bieber (@justinbieber) October 9, 2015
In case you missed Shane Long's spectacular winning goal, here it is again.
YES YES YES!! Come on Ireland #goal #coybig #IREVGER #Long https://t.co/xpxc3G8fhm
— Lenny TodayFM (@MarkLennyskillz) October 8, 2015
In other Bieber news, he's planning on taking legal actions against a publication who released full frontal photos of him to the WORLD. Think those Kate Middleton photos and then some.
